OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAfrican brain drain: '90%  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fof my friends want to      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fleave'                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A new survey of more than 4,500 young  
OL,6, people in Africa, aged 18-24, has found
OL,7, that 52% of them are likely to consider
OL,8, emigrating in the next few years,      
OL,9, citing economic hardship and education 
OL,10, opportunities as the top reasons. The  
OL,11, BBC spoke to five young people in      
OL,12, Nigeria and South Africa who said they 
OL,13, do not feel safe in their countries and
OL,14, lack access to work opportunities, but 
OL,15, for those in Ghana the picture looks   
OL,16, very different.                        
OL,18,F"The Nigerian insecurity is so         
OL,19,Fappalling," says 18-year-old Ayoade Oni
OL,20,Ffrom Lagos. This is one of the main    
OL,21,Freasons he wants to leave Nigeria.     
